        "title": "iRonoc API",
        "version": "v9.1.4",
        "tagline": "Personal portfolio backend exposing GitHub repo/issue lookups, a coffee list, and a donate hook",
        "homepage": "https://ironoc.net",
        "docs_url": "https://ironoc.net/swagger-ui/index.html",
        "license_short": "GPL-3.0 — source code licensed under the GNU General Public License v3.0.",
        "license_md": "- Source code for the underlying project is published under the **GPL-3.0 license**.\n- The API itself is hosted on a personal site (ironoc.net) run by an individual developer; treat availability and rate as best-effort.\n- No published terms of service or commercial SLA — if you build on it, vendor the data or proxy it.\n- CORS is disabled on the documented endpoints, so calls are expected to come from a server, not a browser.",
        "about_md": "`iRonoc API` is the backend behind [ironoc.net](https://ironoc.net), the personal portfolio site of software engineer Conor Heffron. It is a small Spring-style service that mixes a couple of GitHub-proxy endpoints (used to populate the portfolio's repo and issues pages) with a handful of site-specific helpers — a coffee list, a donation hook, and a version probe.\n\nWhat you can actually call:\n\n- `GET /api/get-repo-detail?username={username}` — list a GitHub user's repositories (the portfolio uses this to render Conor's own repos).\n- `GET /api/get-repo-issue/{owner}/{repo}/` — list issues for a specific GitHub repo (example: `conorheffron/ironoc`).\n- Supporting controllers for the site itself: a coffee catalogue, a donation endpoint, a portfolio controller, and a version endpoint.\n\nOperational notes: this is a personal site, not a managed platform. The freepublicapis.com catalogue page reports it as healthy with sub-500ms response times and **CORS disabled**, and no authentication is documented for the public endpoints. Interactive docs live at the [Swagger UI](https://ironoc.net/swagger-ui/index.html). Because the GitHub-facing endpoints ultimately read from GitHub, expect their behaviour and rate to track upstream GitHub limits.",
        "entity_desc": {
          "coffee": "Items from the site's coffee catalogue, served by the coffee controller.",
          "coffee_domain": "Domain/model shape used to describe a coffee entry returned by the coffee endpoints.",
          "donate_rest_controller": "Endpoints behind the site's donate flow.",
          "portfolio_controller": "Endpoints that drive the portfolio pages on ironoc.net.",
          "repository_detail_domain": "Shape of a GitHub repository record returned by `GET /api/get-repo-detail?username={username}`.",
          "repository_issue_domain": "Shape of a GitHub issue record returned by `GET /api/get-repo-issue/{owner}/{repo}/`.",
          "version": "Version/build info endpoint for the deployed service."
        },
        "auth": false
      },
